What I have added to this article is the truth ok. Please accept this respectfully.

/* Episodes */ Episode 2 service updates explaining why the show's regular maître d'hôtel Marino Monferrato was absent from this episode and Matthew Childs temporarily substituted for him as the show's maître d'hôtel to cover for him during his temporary absence from the show until he returned to the show to take back his usual position as the show's maître d'hôtel which he did in episode 10 of this season.

Additionally to provide further clarification on the reason why he was temporarily absent from the show during this season in episodes 2 to 9 Monferrato was absent from these episodes because he was on holiday visiting his family in his native Italy when these episodes were filmed and COVID-19 travel restrictions which were in place at the time between the United States and Italy meant that he could not get back to the United States in time for the filming of these episodes.

Explanation as to why the show's regular maître d'hôtel Marino Monferrato was absent from episodes 2 to 9 of this season during which Matthew Childs temporarily substituted for him as the show's maître d'hôtel to cover his absence until he returned to the show to take back his usual position as the show's maître d'hôtel which he did in episode 10 of this season. The reason why Monferrato was absent from these episodes was because he went on holiday to visit his family in his native Italy.
